summary: My spouse, who had somehow not previously read Good Omens, was positively cackling at my similarity to Aziraphale. I’m not sure...
body:
My spouse, who had somehow not previously read Good Omens, was positively cackling at my similarity to Aziraphale. I’m not sure how to feel about this, other than to say that (a) his argument was backed up by several independent points of evidence, and (b) what finally put the nail in it for him was apparently the first-edition copy of Mrs. Beeton’s Book of Household Management.

This has been, I suppose, your regularly scheduled reminder that we aren’t always the clearest judges of how our own character manifests. No Robert Burns quotes required, even.
